<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> Quoted on the dust jacket of <i>The Age of Extremes</i>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.international.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=7315" class="external text" title="http://www.international.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=7315" rel="nofollow">"Eric Hobsbawm Speaks on His New Memoir"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/University_of_California,_Los_Angeles" title="University of California, Los Angeles">UCLA</a> International Institute</i>, 2004</li>
<li id="cite_note-kamm-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-kamm_25-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,3284-1188437,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,3284-1188437,00.html" rel="nofollow">Oliver Kamm, ‚ÄòIt takes an intellectual to find excuses for Stalinism,‚Äô </a><a href="/wiki/The_Times" title="The Times">The Times</a> July 23, 2004</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> Beichman, Arnold. 2003. The Invitational at Columbia. The <a href="/wiki/Washington_Times" title="Washington Times" class="mw-redirect">Washington Times</a>. Monday, March 31, 2003</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> E. Hobsbawm, 'The Age of Extremes,' 1994 p. 393, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0349106711" class="internal">ISBN 0-349-10671-1</a>)</li>
</ol>
</div>
